// Bun Snapshot v1, https://bun.sh/docs/test/snapshots

exports[`renderDecision matches snapshot 1`] = `
"# Switch inventory to a weight-based carry system
**Post:** post_123
**Participants:** felix, asha

## Decision
We will replace the slot-based inventory with a weight-based system capped per character strength.

## Context
Slot-based inventory was blocking stacking of crafting materials and felt inconsistent with the survival tone of the game.

## Options Considered
### Keep slot-based, add stacking
- **Pros:** Minimal rework
- **Cons:** Still allows carrying unrealistic amounts of heavy gear

### Weight-based with strength cap
- **Pros:** Matches survival tone, encourages loadout decisions
- **Cons:** Requires UI rework and rebalancing all item weights

## Rationale
Weight-based best supports the survival identity even though it costs more UI work up front.

## Non-Goals
- Encumbrance debuffs beyond a hard carry cap

## Open Questions
- Should mounts/pack animals get separate weight pools?
"
`;

